// Negative fixture for nexus-8tee: T-Proj must reject projection on a
// structurally-linear record. Pre-fix, `infer_field_access` only
// looked up the field with no linearity guard, so projection on a
// record carrying a linear field (here `buf: %ByteBuffer`) typechecked
// and even linked cleanly — silently dropping the `%ByteBuffer`
// resource the user never bound.
//
// Post-fix this file MUST fail to typecheck with a T-Proj diagnostic
// naming the linear field that caused structural linearity (`buf`).
//
// Filename intentionally omits `_test` so `nexus test` does not pick
// it up (a fixture that intentionally fails compile would otherwise
// be reported as a runner failure).
import * as bb from "std:bytebuffer"

let main = fn () -> unit do
  let r = { buf: bb.empty(), id: 1 }
  r.id
  return ()
end
